style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Here are the most relevant <strong class=
=3D"font-semibold">open-source</strong> projects and resources for <strong =
class=3D"font-semibold">real-time (online) character recognition from strok=
e data</strong> (e.g., pen/touch input sequences of points), with a focus o=
n approaches that leverage <strong class=3D"font-semibold">character decomp=
osition</strong> (stroke-level, radical/component-level, or structural deco=
mposition). These are primarily for Chinese (CJK) characters, as stroke dec=
omposition is most commonly applied there.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">1. HanziLookup / HanziLookupJS / hanzi_lookup (Recommended for real-t=
ime stroke matching)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Descript=
ion</strong>: Lightweight, browser-based (JavaScript or Rust/WebAssembly) C=
hinese handwriting recognition library. It takes real-time stroke data (arr=
ay of strokes, each an array of 2D points) as input and recognizes characte=
rs by matching against precomputed stroke data. It uses geometric matching =
(direction, position, angle) on stroke paths, drawing from decomposed strok=
e order and medians. Suitable for real-time input (e.g., canvas drawing) wi=
thout heavy ML models.<a href=3D"https://github.com/gugray/hanzi_lookup" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" class=3D"no-copy inlin=
e text-nowrap print:hidden py-[2.5px] ps-2 pe-2 rounded-full align-[0.5px] =
bg-surface-l1 text-[13px] leading-none font-medium !text-fg-secondary hover=
:!text-fg-primary visited:text-fg-secondary focus:outline-none !no-underlin=
e hover:!no-underline citation" data-state=3D"closed">=E2=81=A0Github</a></=
li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition aspect</strong>: Relies on stroke-order vector data and medians deriv=
ed from character decompositions (inspired by Make Me a Hanzi). It handles =
stroke sequences and sub-strokes for matching.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Real-tim=
e</strong>: Yes =E2=80=94 client-side, fast for interactive drawing.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Links</s=
trong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
