l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Real-tim=
e stroke input handling</strong>: Most projects expect stroke data as seque=
nces of points (x, y, sometimes with timestamps or pen-up/down). You can ca=
pture this via HTML Canvas, touch events, or libraries like Paper.js. Norma=
lization (scaling, resampling) is usually needed before matching.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition benefits</strong>: Stroke/radical-level decomposition enables <strong=
 class=3D"font-semibold">zero-shot</strong> or open-vocabulary recognition =
(recognizing unseen characters if their stroke sequence is known) and bette=
r handles variations in writing style/order.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Limitati=
ons</strong>: Pure rule-based/matching approaches (like HanziLookup) are li=
ghtweight and real-time but less robust to noisy/variant writing than deep =
learning models. For higher accuracy, combine with ML (e.g., adapt FudanOCR=
 or train on CASIA-OLHWDB datasets).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Datasets=
 for training/extension</strong>: CASIA online handwriting databases (commo=
n benchmark); Make Me a Hanzi data for strokes.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Related =
papers</strong> (for implementation ideas):<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker=
:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">"Zero-Shot Chinese Character Recognition=
 with Stroke-Level Decomposition" (basis for FudanOCR module).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Many online HCCR papers use RNN/LSTM or =
Transformers on stroke sequences.</li>
</ul></li>
