style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Here are the most relevant <strong class=
=3D"font-semibold">open-source or publicly available datasets</strong> for =
<strong class=3D"font-semibold">handwriting recognition</strong>, with a fo=
cus on <strong class=3D"font-semibold">online/stroke-based data</strong> (s=
equences of (x, y) points with pen-up/down or timestamps) that align with r=
eal-time character recognition and <strong class=3D"font-semibold">characte=
r decomposition</strong> (stroke order, radicals, or structural breakdown).=
 These are especially useful for Chinese (CJK) characters, as stroke decomp=
osition is most powerful there, but I also include strong English/Latin opt=
ions.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Top Datasets for Online Chinese Handwriting Recognition (Stroke Data)=
</h3>
<ol dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">CASIA-OL=
HWDB (CASIA Online Handwritten Chinese Character Database)</strong><ul dir=
=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Descript=
ion</strong>: The gold standard for online HCCR (Handwritten Chinese Charac=
ter Recognition). Contains unconstrained stroke sequences (point trajectori=
es with timing) from 1,020 writers. Includes isolated characters and text l=
ines. Covers ~3,755=E2=80=934,037 classes (GB2312 level-1 + symbols). Total=
 samples: millions (e.g., OLHWDB1.0 has ~1.69M samples).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition relevance</strong>: Stroke data naturally supports decomposition into=
 ordered strokes, radicals, or components. Often used to generate stroke ex=
traction/segmentation labels (e.g., for RHSEDB or papers on stroke-level de=
composition).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Format</=
strong>: Online stroke trajectories (points with coordinates, sometimes pre=
ssure/timing). Paired with offline image versions (CASIA-HWDB).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Access</=
strong>: Free for academic/research use. Main site: <a href=3D"https://nlpr=
.ia.ac.cn/databases/handwriting/home.html" node=3D"[object Object]" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://nlpr.ia.ac.cn/data=
bases/handwriting/home.html</a> (or search for mirrors/downloads via ICDAR =
competitions). Subsets like OLHWDB1.0/1.1/1.2 are commonly used for benchma=
rking.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Use case=
s</strong>: Real-time recognition, stroke matching, zero-shot recognition v=
ia decomposition, training RNN/LSTM/Transformer models on stroke sequences.=
</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Related<=
/strong>: Frequently paired with ICDAR 2013 Online HCCR competition data.<a=
 href=3D"https://nlpr.ia.ac.cn/databases/handwriting/home.html" target=3D"_=
blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" class=3D"no-copy inline text-no=
wrap print:hidden py-[2.5px] ps-2 pe-2 rounded-full align-[0.5px] bg-surfac=
e-l1 text-[13px] leading-none font-medium !text-fg-secondary hover:!text-fg=
-primary visited:text-fg-secondary focus:outline-none !no-underline hover:!=
no-underline citation" data-state=3D"closed">=E2=81=A0Nlpr.ia</a></li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Make Me =
a Hanzi</strong><ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Descript=
ion</strong>: Not raw handwriting samples, but high-quality <strong class=
=3D"font-semibold">stroke-order vector data</strong> (SVG paths, medians/sk=
eletons) for ~9,000+ common simplified/traditional Chinese characters. Incl=
udes decomposition mappings (radicals, components via Ideographic Descripti=
on Sequences).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition relevance</strong>: Core strength =E2=80=94 provides ordered strokes,=
 medians, and etymology/decomposition trees. Perfect as a reference lexicon=
 for matching user-drawn strokes in real-time.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Format</=
strong>: JSON-like dictionary + graphics.txt (SVG paths) + medians for stro=
ke skeletons.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Access</=
strong>: Fully open-source on GitHub: <a href=3D"https://github.com/skishor=
e/makemeahanzi" node=3D"[object Object]" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener =
noreferrer nofollow">https://github.com/skishore/makemeahanzi</a>. Used by =
HanziLookup, Hanzi Writer, etc.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Use case=
s</strong>: Real-time stroke recognition prototypes, animation, or augmenti=
ng CASIA data with canonical stroke order.<a href=3D"https://github.com/ski=
shore/makemeahanzi" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" =
class=3D"no-copy inline text-nowrap print:hidden py-[2.5px] ps-2 pe-2 round=
ed-full align-[0.5px] bg-surface-l1 text-[13px] leading-none font-medium !t=
ext-fg-secondary hover:!text-fg-primary visited:text-fg-secondary focus:out=
line-none !no-underline hover:!no-underline citation" data-state=3D"closed"=
>=E2=81=A0Github</a></li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Other Ch=
inese/Stroke-Focused Datasets</strong><ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text=
-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">MegaHan9=
7K</strong>: Large-scale (97K+ categories) with handwritten, historical, an=
d synthetic subsets supporting GB18030-2022. Addresses long-tail and zero-s=
hot challenges. GitHub: <a href=3D"https://github.com/SCUT-DLVCLab/MegaHan9=
7K" node=3D"[object Object]" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer n=
ofollow">https://github.com/SCUT-DLVCLab/MegaHan97K</a>.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">RHSEDB (=
Regular Handwriting Character Stroke Extraction Dataset)</strong>: Derived =
from CASIA-OLHWDB; provides stroke-segmented labels for decomposition train=
ing.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">SCUT-COU=
CH, TKH_MTH, or Cursive Chinese Calligraphy Dataset</strong>: Additional ha=
ndwritten or artistic variants (see awesome-traditional-chinese-character-r=
ecognition repo for links).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">IHCCD</s=
trong>: Irregular handwritten Chinese characters (smaller, specialized).</l=
i>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">FudanOCR=
 stroke-level-decomposition data</strong>: Includes decompose-stroke files =
from Unicode Han Database for zero-shot matching.</li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Datasets for Japanese/Kanji (Similar Stroke-Based)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">TUAT Nak=
ayosi-t and Kuchibue-d (HANDS databases)</strong>: Large online Japanese ha=
ndwriting datasets (~3M+ patterns from hundreds of writers). Stroke traject=
ories for Kanji and other characters. Available via Nakagawa Lab (TUAT): <a=
 href=3D"http://web.tuat.ac.jp/~nakagawa/database/" node=3D"[object Object]=
" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow">http://web.tuat.ac=
.jp/~nakagawa/database/</a>. Often converted to UNIPEN format. Great for CJ=
K stroke recognition research.<a href=3D"http://web.tuat.ac.jp/~nakagawa/da=
tabase/en/about_nakayosi.html" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer=
 nofollow" class=3D"no-copy inline text-nowrap print:hidden py-[2.5px] ps-2=
 pe-2 rounded-full align-[0.5px] bg-surface-l1 text-[13px] leading-none fon=
t-medium !text-fg-secondary hover:!text-fg-primary visited:text-fg-secondar=
y focus:outline-none !no-underline hover:!no-underline citation" data-state=
=3D"closed">=E2=81=A0Web.tuat</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Datasets for English/Latin Online Handwriting (Stroke Data)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">IAM-OnDB=
 (IAM Online Handwriting Database)</strong>: Online stroke data (lines of t=
ext with timestamps) from 221 writers. Includes raw points and preprocessed=
 features. Excellent for real-time word/line recognition. Often used with L=
STM/CTC models. Access via IAM site (registration required): <a href=3D"htt=
ps://fki.tic.heia-fr.ch/databases/iam-handwriting-database" node=3D"[object=
 Object]" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://fk=
i.tic.heia-fr.ch/databases/iam-handwriting-database</a> (see On-Line sectio=
n).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">IAMonDo<=
/strong>: Online documents with strokes labeled for text, diagrams, etc. (I=
nkML format). Useful for layout + recognition.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">UNIPEN</=
strong>: Older but classic international online handwriting dataset (multip=
le languages).</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Offline (Image-Based) Datasets Often Used Alongside Online</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">CASIA-HW=
DB</strong>: Offline images paired with the online versions above. Useful f=
or hybrid online/offline models or stroke extraction from images.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">IAM Hand=
writing Database</strong> (offline version): Scanned English text lines/wor=
ds (very popular benchmark).</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Tips for Your Use Case (Real-Time Stroke Recognition + Decomposition)=
</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Start wi=
th</strong>: CASIA-OLHWDB (for training robust models on real stroke variat=
ions) + Make Me a Hanzi (for canonical stroke order and decomposition match=
ing). Many projects (e.g., HanziLookup) combine them.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Preproce=
ssing</strong>: Normalize strokes (resampling, scaling, direction features)=
. Use stroke order from Make Me a Hanzi or standards for decomposition.</li=
>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">For deco=
mposition/zero-shot</strong>: Look at papers like "Zero-Shot Chinese Charac=
ter Recognition with Stroke-Level Decomposition" (uses stroke sequences + m=
atching). Datasets like CASIA are commonly adapted for this.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Access N=
otes</strong>: Most CASIA/IAM data require academic registration or contact=
 (free for research). Check GitHub mirrors or Hugging Face for processed ve=
rsions (e.g., CASIA-HWDB lines on HF).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Syntheti=
c Augmentation</strong>: Combine with tools like TextRecognitionDataGenerat=
or or stroke-based generators for more data.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">If you need help w=
ith a specific language (Chinese/Japanese/English), format (stroke sequence=
s vs. images), platform (Python, JS/WebAssembly), or integrating with chara=
cter decomposition code, let me know more details =E2=80=94 e.g., target ac=
curacy, zero-shot needs, or whether you want links to processed versions/lo=
aders. These datasets power most state-of-the-art real-time HCCR systems!</=
