[155%] max-md:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Here =
are the most common and effective <strong class=3D"font-semibold">preproces=
sing techniques for online stroke data</strong> (sequences of (x, y) points=
, often with pen-up/pen-down flags or timestamps) in <strong class=3D"font-=
semibold">real-time handwriting recognition</strong>, especially for <stron=
g class=3D"font-semibold">Chinese/CJK characters</strong> using <strong cla=
ss=3D"font-semibold">stroke-based matching or decomposition</strong>. These=
 steps clean noisy input from touch/pen devices, normalize variations, and =
prepare data for matching against decomposed stroke references (e.g., from =
Make Me a Hanzi) or feeding into models (RNN/LSTM/Transformer or rule-based=
 matchers like HanziLookup).</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">1. Point-Level Cleaning (Noise Reduction)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Remove d=
uplicated / redundant points</strong>: Eliminate consecutive points with id=
entical or near-identical coordinates (common in slow drawing or high sampl=
ing rates). Threshold: e.g., Euclidean distance &lt; 1=E2=80=932 pixels.</l=
i>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Remove h=
ooks and artifacts</strong>: Detect and trim small "hooks" at stroke beginn=
ings/ends caused by pen-down/up jitter. Common method: Use angle change thr=
eshold (e.g., sharp direction changes &gt; 120=E2=80=93150=C2=B0 over few p=
oints) or length threshold (short segments &lt; 5=E2=80=9310% of average st=
roke length).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Remove n=
oise from pen speed variations</strong>: Filter points based on pen speed (=
if timestamp available) to eliminate tremors.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These steps are st=
andard in online handwriting pipelines and significantly reduce matching er=
rors in decomposition-based systems.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">2. Resampling (Uniform Point Distribution)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Equal-di=
stance or equal-time resampling</strong>: Interpolate or downsample points =
so they are evenly spaced along the stroke path (e.g., fixed number of poin=
ts per stroke or fixed distance interval). This makes strokes comparable re=
gardless of drawing speed.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Why impo=
rtant for real-time &amp; decomposition</strong>: Ensures consistent stroke=
 length representation for geometric matching or sequence models. For CJK, =
it helps align user strokes with canonical stroke medians/order from datase=
ts like Make Me a Hanzi.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Common practice: Resample each stroke to=
 20=E2=80=9364 points, or the entire character trajectory to a fixed total =
(e.g., pad to 800 time steps in some models).</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">3. Normalization (Size, Position, and Scale Invariance)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Bounding=
 box normalization</strong>: Translate all points so the character is cente=
red at (0,0) or aligned to a standard origin. Scale the entire character (o=
r per-stroke) to a fixed size, e.g., height/width =3D 1.0 or 64=C3=9764 uni=
ts. Often preserve aspect ratio or use anisotropic scaling.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Characte=
r-level vs. stroke-level</strong>: For decomposition, normalize the whole c=
haracter first, then handle individual strokes.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Rotation=
 / slant correction</strong> (optional but useful for robustness):<ul dir=
=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Compute principal axis (via PCA on point=
s) and rotate to align with horizontal/vertical.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Shear correction for slant (common in le=
ft-to-right writing).</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Hanging =
stroke normalization</strong>: Adjust strokes that "hang" or protrude unusu=
ally.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These make recogni=
tion robust to different writing sizes, positions, and slight rotations=E2=
=80=94critical for real-time canvas input.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">4. Feature Augmentation / Representation</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Directio=
n / delta features</strong>: Compute differences (=CE=94x, =CE=94y) between=
 consecutive points, or stroke direction angles (8 or 16 bins).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Pen stat=
e encoding</strong>: Explicitly mark pen-up/pen-down (e.g., special tokens =
like (-0.01, 0) for pen-up).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Time / s=
peed features</strong> (if available): Normalize timestamps or add velocity=
 as extra dimension.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Skeleton=
 / median extraction</strong>: For advanced decomposition, compute stroke s=
keletons (thinning) or medians to compare against reference decompositions.=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">5. Stroke Segmentation &amp; Ordering</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Detect s=
troke boundaries</strong>: Use pen-up/pen-down events (most online data alr=
eady provides this).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Stroke o=
rder handling</strong>: For CJK decomposition, compare user stroke sequence=
 against standard order (from Unicode Han Database or Make Me a Hanzi). Som=
e systems allow flexible order with matching tolerance.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition-specific prep</strong>: Map strokes to basic types (horizontal, verti=
cal, left-falling, right-falling, turning) for stroke-level decomposition m=
ethods.</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">6. Padding &amp; Sequence Formatting (for Models)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Pad shorter sequences to a fixed maximum=
 length (e.g., 800 points) with special padding tokens.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Convert to tensors or sequences suitable=
 for input (e.g., list of [x, y] or augmented features).</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Typical Preprocessing Pipeline (Recommended Order)</h3>
<ol dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Capture raw strokes from canvas/touch ev=
ents (array of points per stroke).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Clean: Remove duplicates + hooks.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Resample: Uniform spacing.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Normalize: Translate + scale (bounding b=
ox).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">(Optional) Rotate/slant correct + featur=
e extraction (directions).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">For decomposition: Align stroke sequence=
/order and extract types/medians.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Output: Normalized stroke list ready for=
 matching (HanziLookup-style) or model input.</li>
</ol>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Implementation Tips &amp; Code Resources</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Python</=
strong>: Use NumPy/SciPy for vector operations (distance, resampling via in=
terpolation). Libraries like <span class=3D"text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-m=
ono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange=
-300">scipy.interpolate</span> or simple linear resampling work well. For C=
ASIA-OLHWDB processing, many GitHub repos include loaders with these steps =
(e.g., normalize to [0, 64) range, remove redundants).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">JavaScri=
pt/Web (real-time)</strong>: Implement on canvas with point arrays; use sim=
ple loops for cleaning/resampling. HanziLookup and Make Me a Hanzi demos al=
ready include basic normalization.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">For zero=
-shot/decomposition</strong>: After normalization, match user strokes geome=
trically (position, direction, length) against precomputed medians from Mak=
e Me a Hanzi or stroke sequences from FudanOCR-style decomposition.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Data Aug=
mentation</strong> (post-preprocessing): Random scaling, rotation (=C2=B110=
=E2=80=9315=C2=B0), noise addition, or stroke order perturbation to improve=
 robustness.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These techniques a=
re widely used in CASIA-OLHWDB benchmarks and papers on stroke-level decomp=
osition. Proper preprocessing can boost accuracy by 10=E2=80=9330% in match=
ing-based or sequence models, especially for variable real-time input.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">If you need:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Code snippets (Python/JS) for a specific=
 step,</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Integration with HanziLookup or CASIA da=
ta loader,</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Handling for a particular framework (PyT=
orch, TensorFlow, WebAssembly),</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Or focus on offline image-to-stroke conv=
ersion,</li>
</ul>
