[155%] max-md:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Here =
are the key <strong class=3D"font-semibold">stroke segmentation techniques<=
/strong> for <strong class=3D"font-semibold">online handwriting recognition=
</strong> (stroke data as sequences of (x, y) points with pen-up/pen-down),=
 with emphasis on <strong class=3D"font-semibold">real-time applications</s=
trong> and <strong class=3D"font-semibold">character decomposition</strong>=
 for Chinese/CJK characters. Stroke segmentation here refers to breaking th=
e raw trajectory into individual meaningful strokes (or sub-strokes) =E2=80=
=94 essential for matching against canonical decompositions (e.g., from Mak=
e Me a Hanzi), radical/component analysis, or zero-shot recognition.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">1. Rule-Based / Heuristic Techniques (Fast for Real-Time)</h3>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These are lightwei=
ght, suitable for immediate feedback in canvas-based input, and often used =
as the first stage before decomposition matching.</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Pen-Up /=
 Pen-Down Based Segmentation</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text=
-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Natural and simplest: Each pen-down to p=
en-up sequence is one stroke.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Common in online data like CASIA-OLHWDB =
(strokes are already provided this way).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Limitation: In cursive or overlaid writi=
ng, users may not lift the pen, or strokes overlap.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Off-Stro=
ke Distance and Geometric Features</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marke=
r:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Group strokes or split trajectories usin=
g:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Distance between consecutive strokes (of=
f-stroke gaps).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Bounding box overlap of adjacent strokes=
.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Direction changes (sharp angles, e.g., &=
gt;90=E2=80=93120=C2=B0 turns).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Stroke speed/velocity (slowdowns at stro=
ke ends).</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Additional features: Stroke vector (dire=
ction histograms, 8 or 16 bins) and speed profiles.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Used in over-segmentation for text lines=
/words, then refined for characters.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Over-Seg=
mentation Approaches</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-seconda=
ry">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Intentionally split more aggressively (e=
.g., at every potential junction or direction change) to create primitive s=
egments.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Then use candidate lattice + path search=
 (combining geometric context, character recognition scores, and language m=
odels) to merge into valid characters.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Effective for unconstrained or cursive C=
hinese handwriting.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These heuristics a=
re fast (O(n) per character) and integrate well with decomposition: after s=
egmentation, map strokes to basic types (horizontal, vertical, left-falling=
, right-falling, hook/turning =E2=80=94 per GB18030 standard) for structura=
l matching.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">2. Model-Based and Learning-Based Techniques</h3>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">For higher robustn=
ess to noisy, cursive, or variable writing styles.</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Skeleton=
ization + Query Pixel Guided Extraction</strong> (Offline-to-Online Bridge)=
:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Use Fully Convolutional Network (FCN) or=
 SkeNet for skeleton extraction from rendered stroke images.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Query pixel guidance to trace individual=
 strokes from skeleton branches.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Model-based matching to resolve ambiguit=
ies at intersections/crossings (e.g., using stroke consistency models like =
PathNet).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Reported high precision (89=E2=80=9395%)=
 on datasets derived from CASIA-OLHWDB and ICDAR-2013 Online.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Good for decomposition: Produces clean i=
ndividual strokes for comparison with reference medians or radicals.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Deep Lea=
rning Stroke Extraction</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-seco=
ndary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Structur=
e Deformable Image Registration + Semantic Segmentation</strong>: Register =
reference stroke templates (from Make Me a Hanzi or standard order) to the =
input, then use SegNet-like networks for preliminary separation into stroke=
 categories (often 7 classes), followed by fine single-stroke extraction.</=
li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLOv8n-=
seg with Attention</strong> (e.g., Coordinate-Aware Attention): Instance se=
gmentation variant for fine stroke boundaries, handling intersections via m=
ulti-label outputs.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Stroke-S=
eg Framework</strong>: Multi-label output for intersecting regions + prior =
knowledge vector (stroke composition per character) to guide segmentation.<=
/li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">These handle complex glyphs where stroke=
s cross or touch.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Graph-Ba=
sed or Trajectory Parsing</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-se=
condary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Treat strokes as graphs; use Dynamic Gra=
ph Attention (DyGAT) for classification and segmentation in documents/sketc=
hes.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Trajectory recovery models (e.g., PEN-Ne=
t with double-stream parsing) for complex glyphs.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">3. Techniques Specific to Character Decomposition</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Stroke T=
ype Classification + Ordering</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:tex=
t-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Classify segmented strokes into the 5=E2=
=80=938 basic types.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Match sequence and spatial relations (re=
lative position, direction) against decomposition trees (Ideographic Descri=
ption Sequences or Make Me a Hanzi data).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Enables zero-shot recognition for unseen=
 characters if decomposition is known.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Radical/=
Component-Level Segmentation</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text=
-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Trajectory-based Radical Analysis Networ=
k: Segments into radicals first, then finer strokes.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Hierarchical approaches: Coarse (radical=
) =E2=86=92 Fine (stroke) using deformable registration.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Referenc=
e-Guided Matching</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary"=
>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">After initial segmentation, align user s=
trokes to canonical templates via deformable registration or geometric matc=
hing (position, length, angle).</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Recommended Pipeline for Real-Time + Decomposition</h3>
<ol dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Capture<=
/strong> raw points from canvas/touch (with pen-up/down).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Clean &a=
mp; Preprocess</strong> (as discussed previously: remove duplicates/hooks, =
resample, normalize bounding box).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Initial =
Segmentation</strong>: Pen-up/down + geometric heuristics (distance, angle,=
 speed).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Refineme=
nt (if needed)</strong>: Over-segmentation =E2=86=92 candidate merging, or =
lightweight DL for ambiguous cases.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Decompos=
ition Alignment</strong>: Classify stroke types =E2=86=92 match order/posit=
ion against reference (Make Me a Hanzi medians or FudanOCR decompose files)=
.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Output</=
strong>: Ordered list of segmented strokes ready for recognition/matching.<=
/li>
</ol>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">This pipeline is e=
fficient for real-time (heuristics &lt;10ms per character on modest hardwar=
e) and boosts accuracy in decomposition-based systems like HanziLookup.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Open-Source Implementations &amp; Resources</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">MengLi-l=
1/StrokeExtraction</strong> (GitHub): Deep learning stroke extraction using=
 structure deformable registration + semantic segmentation. Includes RHSEDB=
 dataset derived from CASIA-OLHWDB with single-stroke labels. Excellent for=
 offline images but adaptable (render online strokes to images).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">FudanOCR=
</strong> stroke-level-decomposition module: Uses decomposition files for m=
atching segmented strokes.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">HanziLoo=
kup / Make Me a Hanzi</strong>: Implicit segmentation via pen events + geom=
etric matching against pre-decomposed stroke paths.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Papers with code often reference CASIA-O=
LHWDB processing scripts (search GitHub for "CASIA OLHWDB stroke segmentati=
on").</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Challenges &amp; Tips</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Cursive/=
Overlaid Writing</strong>: Heuristics fail; use learning-based or over-segm=
entation + recognition feedback.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Intersec=
tions/Crossings</strong>: Major error source =E2=80=94 addressed by model-b=
ased matching or multi-label segmentation.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Real-Tim=
e Trade-off</strong>: Prioritize heuristics for instant feedback; fallback =
to DL for verification.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Evaluati=
on</strong>: Use precision on stroke extraction (e.g., from RHSEDB or ICDAR=
 benchmarks).</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">These techniques d=
irectly support your earlier pipeline (preprocessing =E2=86=92 segmentation=
