<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">After rendering, p=
ass the image through the model's pipeline (SDNet =E2=86=92 SegNet =E2=86=
=92 ExtractNet) to get separated stroke masks. These can then be matched ag=
ainst reference decompositions from <strong class=3D"font-semibold">Make Me=
 a Hanzi</strong> for recognition or zero-shot tasks.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Tips for Your Use Case</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Real-tim=
e adaptation</strong>: Inference is reasonably fast on GPU. For web/canvas =
input, render on-the-fly in JS/Python backend, then run the PyTorch model (=
or export to ONNX/TorchScript for faster deployment).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Integrat=
ion with decomposition</strong>: The output single-stroke images align well=
 with stroke-order data from Make Me a Hanzi or FudanOCR's decompose files.=
</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Customiz=
ation</strong>: Start by training on RHSEDB, then fine-tune with your own r=
endered CASIA-OLHWDB data.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Challeng=
es</strong>: Model expects normalized handwritten-style images; test with y=
our preprocessed strokes.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
