:first-child]:mt-0"><p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:l=
eading-[155%] max-md:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;=
">Here's a detailed comparison between <strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLO=
v8n-seg-CAA-BiFPN</strong> (2024) and <strong class=3D"font-semibold">Strok=
eExtraction</strong> (Meng Li et al., AAAI 2023 Oral) for <strong class=3D"=
font-semibold">Chinese character stroke segmentation</strong> in the contex=
t of your real-time handwriting recognition + character decomposition pipel=
ine.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Both models take r=
endered character images (e.g., from preprocessed online stroke data) as in=
put and aim to separate individual or typed strokes, handling intersections=
/touchings common in handwritten CJK characters. However, they differ signi=
ficantly in approach, strengths, and suitability.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">1. Core Approach &amp; Architecture</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLOv8n-=
seg-CAA-BiFPN</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Instance segmentation model based on Ult=
ralytics <strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLOv8n-seg</strong> (nano variant=
 for lightness).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Key enhancements:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=
=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Coordina=
te-Aware Attention (CAA)</strong>: Divides features for differentiated atte=
ntion in horizontal/vertical/channel dimensions; better captures stroke pos=
ition regularity and intersections.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Enhanced=
 BiFPN</strong>: Improved multi-scale feature fusion (down to P2 layer) wit=
h weighted learnable fusion and ReLU normalization.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Shape-Io=
U Loss</strong>: Replaces standard CIoU for better handling of fine, elonga=
ted stroke shapes.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">End-to-end: Detects + segments strokes a=
s instances with bounding boxes and masks.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">StrokeEx=
traction</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Multi-stage pipeline tailored specifical=
ly for stroke extraction:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">SDNet</s=
trong> (Structure Deformable Image Registration): Registers canonical refer=
ence stroke templates (prior knowledge of stroke order/composition) to the =
input image.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">SegNet</=
strong> (Semantic Segmentation): Preliminary classification into ~7 basic s=
troke categories using semantic features.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">ExtractN=
et</strong>: Refines to high-precision single-stroke masks, resolving ambig=
uities at crossings via model-based matching.</li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Leverages <strong class=3D"font-semibold=
">stroke priors</strong> (e.g., reference order from datasets like Make Me =
a Hanzi or standard decompositions) + semantic features.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class=3D"f=
ont-semibold">Winner for decomposition</strong>: StrokeExtraction =E2=80=94=
 its explicit use of stroke priors and reference registration aligns direct=
ly with character decomposition (stroke order, radicals, zero-shot matching=
).</p>
