<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLOv8n-=
seg-CAA-BiFPN</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Inference time: <strong class=3D"font-se=
mibold">0.027 seconds</strong> per image (very fast).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Model size: <strong class=3D"font-semibo=
ld">4.8 MB</strong> (smaller than original YOLOv8n-seg at 6.5 MB).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Lightweight design =E2=86=92 excellent f=
or real-time canvas input (render =E2=86=92 segment =E2=86=92 decompose).</=
li>
</ul></li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">StrokeEx=
traction</strong>:<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Multi-stage (registration + segmentation=
 + extraction) =E2=86=92 likely slower than single-shot YOLO (no exact numb=
ers published, but modular nature suggests higher latency).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Better suited for offline/batch processi=
ng or accuracy-critical verification.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class=3D"f=
ont-semibold">Winner for real-time</strong>: YOLOv8n-seg-CAA-BiFPN (faster,=
 smaller, easier deployment).</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">4. Strengths &amp; Weaknesses for Your Pipeline</h3>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class=3D"f=
ont-semibold">YOLOv8n-seg-CAA-BiFPN</strong>:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Pros</st=
rong>: Extremely lightweight &amp; fast; strong on fine stroke boundaries; =
easy to integrate (Ultralytics ecosystem, ONNX export, mobile/GPU friendly)=
; good generalization on handwritten/calligraphy variants in CCSE datasets.=
</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Cons</st=
rong>: Less explicit use of stroke order/priors =E2=86=92 may require extra=
 post-processing for decomposition (e.g., matching masks to Make Me a Hanzi=
 references or FudanOCR stroke types). Pure instance segmentation without b=
uilt-in registration.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class=3D"f=
ont-semibold">StrokeExtraction</strong>:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Pros</st=
rong>: Designed for high-precision single-stroke extraction with priors =E2=
=86=92 directly supports character decomposition, stroke ordering, and zero=
-shot scenarios. Handles complex crossings better via deformable registrati=
on + semantic guidance. Modular (train individual parts).</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Cons</st=
rong>: More complex pipeline (harder to optimize for ultra-low latency); re=
po focuses on research with less emphasis on deployment speed/metrics; requ=
ires reference templates.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class=3D"f=
ont-semibold">Overall for real-time + decomposition</strong>:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Use <strong class=3D"font-semibold">YOLO=
v8n-seg-CAA-BiFPN</strong> if priority is <strong class=3D"font-semibold">s=
peed and ease</strong> (e.g., interactive web/canvas app). Render normalize=
d strokes =E2=86=92 run segmentation =E2=86=92 post-process masks for type/=
order matching.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal">Use <strong class=3D"font-semibold">Stro=
keExtraction</strong> if priority is <strong class=3D"font-semibold">accura=
cy and decomposition fidelity</strong> (e.g., robust matching against canon=
ical stroke data). It integrates naturally with Make Me a Hanzi or CASIA-de=
rived priors.</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">5. Implementation &amp; Integration Tips</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
